# UniSchedule AI — Core Project Context

**Project:** Intelligent University Meeting Scheduler (Final Year Project, University of Canterbury).

**Read for full context:** `docs/PROJECT-NOTES.md` and `docs/supervisor-submission/05-system-design-pack.md`.

## Tech stack (do not change without user approval)

| Layer | Stack |
|-------|--------|
| Frontend | Next.js + TypeScript |
| Backend | Laravel REST API |
| Database | MySQL + Eloquent |
| Auth | **Laravel Sanctum** (not custom JWT) — `auth:sanctum` on protected routes |

**Architecture:** Next.js → HTTPS → Laravel API → MySQL. NLP/LLM called from Laravel; scheduling decisions validated deterministically (hybrid AI).

## Research priorities (supervisor requirement)

- Measurable RQs, literature gap, methodology, evaluation — not code-only work
- Evaluation: manual vs AI-assisted scheduling, clash metrics, UAT
- References: **Harvard** format in dissertation docs

## MoSCoW — Must have

Auth (Sanctum) + roles; meeting CRUD; clash detection; academic constraints; NLP/hybrid input; room allocation; survey + evaluation.

## Won't have (defer to Future Work)

Voice assistant, mobile app, LMS integration, ML preference learning, multi-campus enterprise deploy.

